---
/**
 * rest-api/0005 · Figure 3 — "three placements, one trade-off each".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0005-api-versioning-strategies.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. This figure uses no arrowhead
 * markers, so it needs no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 220"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Three placement strategies: URI path, custom header, and media-type negotiation, each with one trade-off"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THREE PLACEMENTS · ONE TRADE-OFF EACH</text
            >
            <!-- 1 URI path -->
            <rect
                x="8"
                y="32"
                width="200"
                height="172"
                rx="10"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="108"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">1 · URI PATH</text
            >
            <rect x="22" y="62" width="172" height="30" rx="6" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="108"
                y="82"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-family="ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace"
                fill="#111110">GET /v2/users</text
            >
            <text
                x="108"
                y="112"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓ visible · routes &amp;</text
            >
            <text
                x="108"
                y="125"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">caches by URL · browser-</text
            >
            <text
                x="108"
                y="138"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">testable · most common</text
            >
            <line x1="22" y1="150" x2="194" y2="150" stroke="#d8d4c8"></line>
            <text
                x="108"
                y="166"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">✗ trade-off: couples</text
            >
            <text x="108" y="179" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >version to identity —</text
            >
            <text x="108" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >"not pure REST"</text
            >
            <!-- 2 custom header -->
            <rect
                x="220"
                y="32"
                width="200"
                height="172"
                rx="10"
                fill="#eef2f5"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">2 · CUSTOM HEADER</text
            >
            <rect x="234" y="62" width="172" height="30" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="81"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-family="ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace"
                fill="#111110">Accept-Version: 2</text
            >
            <text
                x="320"
                y="112"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓ clean, version-free</text
            >
            <text
                x="320"
                y="125"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">URLs · resource keeps</text
            >
            <text
                x="320"
                y="138"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">one identity</text
            >
            <line x1="234" y1="150" x2="406" y2="150" stroke="#d8d4c8"></line>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="166"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">✗ trade-off: invisible —</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="179" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >easy to forget, hard to</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >test &amp; spot in logs</text
            >
            <!-- 3 media type -->
            <rect
                x="432"
                y="32"
                width="200"
                height="172"
                rx="10"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="532"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">3 · MEDIA TYPE</text
            >
            <rect x="446" y="60" width="172" height="34" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
            <text
                x="532"
                y="76"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="8"
                font-family="ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace"
                fill="#111110">Accept: application/</text
            >
            <text
                x="532"
                y="88"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="8"
                font-family="ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace"
                fill="#111110">vnd.api+json;version=2</text
            >
            <text
                x="532"
                y="112"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓ most "RESTful" ·</text
            >
            <text
                x="532"
                y="125"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">HATEOAS-friendly ·</text
            >
            <text
                x="532"
                y="138"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">version per representation</text
            >
            <line x1="446" y1="150" x2="618" y2="150" stroke="#d8d4c8"></line>
            <text
                x="532"
                y="166"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">✗ trade-off: complex,</text
            >
            <text x="532" y="179" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >poor tooling/proxy</text
            >
            <text x="532" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >support — no ergonomics</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Azure's guidance frames these the same way: there's no universally right answer — the choice
        follows your clients and tooling, not dogma. In an interview, state your pick <em>and</em>
        name its trade-off.<sup><a href="#s3">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
